<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[708,1303,614,1037]" lastBlockId="18.[96,1303,1044,2655]" pageId="18" pageNumber="709">
A member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1841" box="[973,1096,732,761]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropodidae" genus="Macropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="18" pageNumber="709" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachyotis">brachyotis</taxonomicName>
species group which also includes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1926" box="[995,1129,776,801]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropodidae" genus="Petrogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="18" pageNumber="709" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilkinsi">P. wilkinsi</taxonomicName>
, P. burbidge:, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gould" authorityYear="1842" box="[778,935,807,840]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropodidae" genus="Petrogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="18" pageNumber="709" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="concinna">P. concinna</taxonomicName>
. Formerly included eastern and central Northern Territory populations, but these reinstated as a distinct species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1926" box="[830,966,929,958]" class="Mammalia" family="Macropodidae" genus="Petrogale" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="18" pageNumber="709" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wilkinsi">P. wilkinsi</taxonomicName>
) in 2014. Deep genetic divisions exist between the two subspecies and across the Kimberly, suggesting that populations may represent distinct species; further investigation required. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="709" type="synonymic_list">
